[{"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion M\u00fcnchen S-2198 B - 63 St 216S-2198EStG: 21aEStDV: 82aIncome tax treatment of the installation or renewal of heating systems in owner-occupied homes The main features of the planned funding measures that have become known: 1 The federal government and the parliamentary groups of the CDU / CSU and the FDP in the German Bundestag have announced that they consider it necessary - in accordance with a Bavarian initiative - to install new heating and heating systems, especially for environmental reasons Special tax incentives for hot water systems in buildings"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "The two parliamentary groups therefore intend to ensure that an authorization is included in the income tax law in one of the next tax laws due to be passed, according to which the federal government, with the consent of the Bundesrat, will use the already existing benefit in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "Section 82a of the Income Tax Implementation Ordinance (EStDV) can expand to include the installation of new heating and hot water systems, provided the buildings are at least 10 years old"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "This means that in the systems mentioned - as already now with certain energy-saving measures - in the future 10% per year for 10 years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "the investment costs can be written off for tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "The new funding is to apply to systems that are installed after June 30, 1985"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "It will not only be effective for the installation of new heating and hot water systems, but z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "also include the replacement of old boilers, burners or regulation and control equipment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "The two parliamentary groups will bring about a corresponding decision in the finance committee of the German Bundestag as soon as possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "It is assumed that the Federal Government will immediately exhaust the authorization - in accordance with the declaration of intent of the Federal Cabinet of 1 July 1985 - after the law has been passed and will put into effect the funding for installations completed after 30 June 1985"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "The new regulation will essentially be of importance for owner-occupied and therefore flat-rate taxed homes (\u00a7 21a EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "The increased deductions according to \u00a7 82a EStDV are - as before - to be claimed in the annual income tax return (line 11 of Annex V)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "Any special forms or requests are therefore not required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "2 The new version of the authorization regulation in Section 51 Paragraph 1 No. 2 Letter q EStG is not yet known"}, {"meta": {"name": "0062729.xml"}, "text": "--- Income tax / wage tax / church taxBavaria heating system funding installation renewal replacement boiler"}]